methods.javadoc:
Get the cached block whose first entry-point is addr. 
 This method is slightly more efficient than getBlockWithEntryAt,
 however, it should only be used when the cached block has exactly
 one entry-point.
@return the block with an entry-point address of addr, or null of
 the block was not found.
methods.name: getBlockAt
methods.comment:

return.comment:

methods.name: getBlockWithEntryAt
methods.comment: Get the cached block which has an entry-point of addr.

return.comment:
the block with an entry-point address of addr, or null of
 the block was not found.

methods.name: getBlocksContaining
methods.comment: Get all cached blocks which contain addr.

return.comment:
blocks that contain addr if they are in the cache.
          Otherwise, return null.

methods.javadoc:
Get the first block which contains addr.
@return the block whose entry point is minimum among all
          blocks that contain addr and are in the cache.
          Otherwise, return null.
methods.name: getFirstBlockContaining
methods.comment: Get the first block which contains addr.

return.comment:
the block whose entry point is minimum among all
          blocks that contain addr and are in the cache.
          Otherwise, return null.
